column2: Cloudy and ripples on the water.
.5" rain.  Did not give Secchi depth.
Algae appearing .5" rain 16 August- sunny w/ ripples
Less surface algae- .9" rain last week- overcast- ripples.
There was 1.9" rain September 3rd.  Sunny with ripples on the water.
Too windy and rainy to take Secchi reading.
Rain since previous reading- sunny- calm- scattered clouds- and this is the 1st day of sun in a week.
There is no sun.  The lake is too rough to take Secchi reading.
There has been 0.32" rain since previous reading.
Ice out 4/12/87- May readings are before gauge was rechecked.
Assumed sample time was noon.  Did not give Secchi depth.
Slight wind- slight algae bloom- ripples on water- and sunny.
It has been extremely hot for the past few days- temperature is 93 degrees F in the shade.
There is more algae bloom than last year.
Sunny with scattered clouds- waves but no white caps- and there are more power boats than ever before.
Calm and sunny.  There was hardly any boat traffic on Monday.
Calm and sunny.  Heavy rain- over 1" this week.
Much rain and heat previous week.  The weather is sunny and there are ripples on the water.
Algae starting to appear floating on top- very calm and sunny - almost like glass.
Sunny- algae floating on top next to shore.
Sunny- scattered clouds- little boat activity- water choppy.
Slight wind- sunny with some clouds.
Cloudy- ripples- almost no traffic on the lake for two weeks.
Sunny- windy- waves but no white caps- little if any boat activity- last reading for the season.
Some algae throughout the water - much more visible than last week.
Department of Natural Resources adjusted meter gauge possibly making previous readings invalid- lake lower than June 1.
About .5" rain over weekend.- hot and sunny all week.
A lot of black muck washed ashore over the past 2 weeks and more silt on the bottom than ever- lots of strong east winds.
2" rain since last reading- ripples- scattered clouds.
Heavy winds last night but clarity is the same- sunny- ripples- windy
Over 2" rain during week- sunny- some waves- no  wind
Scum gone today-blew up on shore- over 3" rain during previous wk
Windy- scattered clouds and sunny- Assumed time was 12:00. did not give secchi depth.
Partly cloudy- SW wind- 60 F- slight ripples
Overcast- morning rain- 62 F- weeds at shore- slimy- muck- odor
Sunny- 60 F- mod. breeze- water clear @ shore w/ muck and many tadpoles
Clear- sunny- moderate breeze- 69 F- moderate waves- no whitecaps
Clear- sunny- mod. breeze- 67 F- mod. waves- no rain in several weeks
Clear- sunny- light breeze- 55 F- slight ripples- .25" rain Tuesday-new lake level-staff gauge moved
Overcast- 1 in. rain overnight- mod.  SE breeze- slight ripples- 70 F
Overcast- 74 F- strong NE wind with whitecaps
Mod. SW wind- mod. waves- sunny- 72 F- clear- weeds due to lake level drop- dry
Sunny- clear- slight breeze- 68 F- numerous sea gulls on lake
Sunny- clear- slight breeze- medium waves- 60 F- one loon sighted 100 Ft. from boat
Overcast- 1.5 in. rain today- slight. breeze- mod. waves- 66 F- one loon sighted
Slight overcast- slight ripples and breeze- 62 F- .25 in. rain last night- 3 loons sighted
Mod. breeze and waves- sunny- clear- 50 F- wind northeast- 8 mallards on lake- Canadian geese flying south
Sunny- 62 F- slight. SE breeze- ripples- few clouds- colors changing- 1 eagle seen
Sunny- slight N wind- ripples- 50 F- clear- 1 loon- 5 mallards- 1 seagull
Sunny- clear- 44 F- 1 loon- 12 mallards- several gulls- removed staff gauge today- last report
Sunny- clear- 50 F- mod. SW wind- level 5/9 1.38'- 2 loons on lake
Partly cloudy- 60 F- N wind- mod. waves- .3" rain
Cloudy- rainy- 68 F- S wind 10 mph- humidity high- white caps- 1.1" rain overnight
Partly sunny- calm- 60 F- heavy algae along shore- .6" rain 6/18
Sunny- 70 F- SW wind calm- heavy buildup of green along shore
Overcast- windy- white caps- 72 F- humid
Partly sunny- 65 F- mod. NW wind and waves- 3 gulls- 2 loons- 1 blue heron
Partly cloudy- mod. SE wind- 70 F- .3" rain last night- level lowest this year
Sunny- mild SW wind.  The rainfall from 7/16-7/20 was 0.36".
Mod. NE wind- partly cloudy- 72 F- 3 loons sighted- level near record low
Calm- 60 F- 1.9" rain 7/29- 4 gulls- mallard w/ 8 chicks- 1 blue heron
Sunny- SE winds- 72 F- white caps- lake near all time low- 4 fishermen near shore
Sunny- mild NW wind- 68 F- 3 seagulls
Sunny- NW wind- 83 F- white caps
Trace of rain- 52 F- NE wind- slight fog- rain 2.7" this week- 7 mallards on lake
Sunny- mild NW wind- algae- brown foam.  The rainfall from 8/14-9/10 was 5.97".
Calm- 56 F- heavy algae bloom- .3" rain yesterday- trees changing- 2 flocks Canadian geese going S 9/17
S wind- 62 F- whitecaps- algae heavy near shore- colors turning- sighted bald eagle- 8 mallards
Sunny- W wind- the temperature is 36 degrees F- and the algae is clearing slightly.  The rainfall from 9/11-10/9 was 3.65".
Cloudy- SW wind- lake calm- rain .4"- algae clearing- last reading

Partly cloudy day- temp is 52 degrees- winds SW and mild- lake level rose approx. 2" since 4/16 resulting in some murky weed conditions along shore. today one bald eagle and two loons were sighted.  Love the loon call.

Temp is 80 degrees- humidity is high- winds mild southwest- no precipitation for the last 6 days.  Rain in the forecast for tonight.  Mosquitoes and insects abundant.  14 purple martins at our birdhouse.
Mild winds southwest- temp 75 degrees- partly sunny day- very humid.  Abundance of mosquitoes on shore.  Bald eagle sighted over lake- morning rains .10"
Semi-cloudy day with rain showers- temp is 73 degrees- winds mild southwest- spotted 2 killdeer birds on shore- one bald eagle in flight- 6 mallard ducks on lake- and 2 loons.
Light clouds- sunny day- temp is 62 degrees- slight breeze southwest- sound of the loon on lake.  Many small shiner minnows along sandy shore.  Some weed buildup also by shore.
Clear sunny day- mild winds southwest- temp is 64 degrees.  Rain last night .125."  one blue heron flying across lake- the cry of two loons on lake- and one eagle in flight.
Temp is 79 degrees- winds mild w.  Department of Natural Resources checking fish nets for their records.  One eagle sighted in flight- two blue herons- two loons on lake- and four mallard ducks.
Sunny day- mild winds- temp 78 degrees.
Mild winds southwest- temp is 80 degrees- morning rain trace .01."  spotted 8 mallard ducks- one loon and one blue heron.
Winds mild N- semi-cloudy day- temp is 75 degrees.  Sighted one seagull- one loon- and one blue heron on lake.
Sunny day- SW winds with white caps on lake- lake is rough.  Rain this morning was .8".  Temp is 82 degrees and  humid.
The rainfall from 4/16-7/23 was 10.53".  Rain today- the temperature is 59 degrees- winds southwest are mild- algal bloom more pronounced.
Sunny day- very humid- winds are southwest- temp is 78 degrees.  More vacationers out.  Boating increasing for fishing and recreational purposes.
Semi-cloudy day- temp is 69 degrees- winds are southwest.  One bald eagle sighted and one loon sighted over lake.

Sunny day with mild winds from the west- temperature is 86 degrees.  There is three boats pulling skiers on the lake- six boats with fishermen and many swimmers.  The rainfall from 7/32-8/12 was 1.96".

Semi-cloudy day- mild winds are northwest- temp is 70 degrees.  One sea gull on lake- near boat- three loon watch signs posted by Department of Natural Resources.  At west bay heard the cry of one loon last night.
Hazy morning- temperature is 84 degrees- winds are southwest- very humid- white caps on lake.  One loon sighted on lake- purple martins left the birdhouse heading south.
Sunny day- temp is 65 degrees- winds mild from the se- clear skies- mild waves.  One raccoon spotted near shore.
Overcast day- trace of rain- slight green algal blooms- temperature is 62 degrees- and southwest winds.  Rainfall from 8/13-9/10 was 3.9".
Overcast- rainy day- temp is 55 degrees- winds are from the se- colorama starting with leave fall.  One loon spotted and thirteen mergansers on lake- algae bloom more pronounced.
Cloudy day- temp is 45 degrees- mild winds from southwest- colorama getting very pronounced.  No fisherman sighted on lake.  Two bald eagles sighted on lake and 19 mergansers sighted on lake.
Sunny day- the temperature is 65 degrees- west winds- colorama beautiful- in progress the algal blooms are fully pronounced.  The rainfall from 9/10-10/2 was 2.2".
Sunny day- temp is 54 degrees- winds from southwest- colorama at its' peak.  Windy conditions on lake but no whitecaps.  Algal bloom pretty pronounced.
Conditions on lake are windy with whitecaps- the wind is from the southwest- temperature is 36 degrees- time to take in boat- motor- and pier.

White caps on lake- very windy- winds from south.  Temperature is 68 degrees.  Two loons- four mallard ducks and one bald eagle sighted on lake.  First time out this year with new motor boat and doing good!
Mild winds so- temp is 60 degrees- clear blue sky.  One loon sighted at west bay of lake.  On shore sighted purple martins occupying birdhouse.
Winds southwest- temp 65 degrees- frost last night- low 30 degrees- four mallard ducks sighted on lake- many fisherman and boating for memorial day weekend.

Winds mild southwest.- temp is 74 degrees- evenings cool to 50 degrees.  Time to plant that vegetable garden.  Today I spotted four mallard ducks- one loon and the bald eagle.  Many purple martins occupying the birdhouse.
Winds mild from se- temperature is 64 degrees- overnight low 42 degrees.  Two mallard ducks sighted on lake.  Numerous purple martins nesting in both our birdhouses.  Tree swallows at neighbors site.

Temp 48 degrees winds mild southwest. trace of rain today. overcast day slight frost expected tonight- very little rain and the lake is still receding.  Rain gauge reading from 1/20-6/19 is 6.73 inches.
Temp 49 degrees- winds southwest- rain and overcast day.  Evenings cool in lower 40's- record for this time of year.
Calm and sunny day.  Clear blue sky.  Lake very calm- winds southwest- temp is 64 degrees- and sighted bald eagle over lake today.
Semi cloudy day- temp is 71 degrees- winds s- humidity high.  Rain yesterday .275."  couple of skiers and a half dozen fishing boats.  Sighted one loon- and one blue heron.
Temp 66- slight algal bloom along shoreline- spotted a young bald eagle and blue heron over lake.  Rain gauge reading from 6/19-7/15 is 4.06 inches.

Overcast day- temp 61 degrees- winds southwest- rain in the forecast.  Lake very calm- very little algal bloom along shore.  Sighted the bald eagle flying over the lake.  A few mallard ducks on lake.  Not many ducks this year.

Sunny morning- temp 62 degrees- winds southwest- white caps on lake.  Very little algal bloom along shore.  Two fawns on shore as I approached our boat landing.  Yesterday I sighted tow red foxes playing on shore.

Trace of rain .01" early this morning.  Sunny day after- temp 65 degrees- winds s- lake waves with white caps.  Sighted one mother mallard duck with fine young.  Chased a baby fawn from my vegetable garden this morning.
Temp is 58 degrees- winds s- lake conditions rough- sighted one bald eagle catching a fish- also two families of mallard ducks- mother with six babies- And a mother with two babies.
Temp 64- slight algal bloom along shoreline- lake rough with whitecaps.  Rain gauge reading from 7/15-8/17 is 1.65 inches.
Temp is 50 degrees- winds mild from south.  Sunny morning- semi cloudy skies.  Spotted the bald eagle over lake.  Yesterday I saw a porcupine near my garden.
Temp is 52 degrees- winds se- overcast day and rain.  Algae along shores is minimal- spotted the blue heron and bald eagle on lake.  Two white tail deer in the garden as I approached the shore.
Temp is 54 degrees- winds southwest- white caps on lake.  Observed very little algal bloom.  Two families of mallard ducks and one blue heron on lake.

The temperature is 68 degrees- south wind- algae bloom minimal- semi cloudy day- 0.3" of rain this morning- lake very calm- six mallard ducks- and one seagull spotted on the lake. rain gauge reading from 8/18-9/14 is 3.56".
Temperature is 46 degrees- winds s- white caps on lake and very rough.  25 mallards gathered in a group on lake.
Sunny day- temp 62 degrees- winds mild southwest.  Colorama in full.  Ten mallard ducks spotted- and one blue heron on lake- algal bloom is minimal.
Temp 52- winds moderate with white caps on lake- algal bloom appears minimal- night temperatures drop to the high 30's..  Rain gauge reading from 8/18-10/6 is 6.77 inches.
Temp. 50- slight NW breeze- spotted 4 mallard ducks- 2 blue herons and 1 bald eagle- ice is off. partly cloudy with chance of rain. purple martins at bird house.
Medium NW wind- partly cloudy- air temp 54- ducks- blue herons- purple martens- finches.
Few clouds- air temp 56- mild NW winds- rains past four days
Rain- mild winds- air temp 55- 1.62" rain in last five days- foam along shoreline- eagle and heron spotted
Some foam conditions along shoreline- lake level increased due to 10 days of rain so far this month- algal bloom slight.
Air temp 62- SW mild winds- cloudy- blue heron- bald eagle- loon- 7 mallards
Air temp 70- NW winds- partly cloudy- more shoreline vegetation- blue heron- ducklings- bald eagle
Air temp 65- mild SW winds- sunny- algal bloom appearing- purple martins near shoreline birdhouse- training young to fly
Temp 56 F- white caps on lake- algal bloom minimal- some foam appearing along shoreline with mixing of lake.

Temp is 49 degrees- winds are mild- southwest. semi-cloudy day.  Algal bloom is minimal.  Some sea gulls on the lake.  Spotted the bald eagle carrying a large fish- and was unable to hold it in flight.  Purple martins migrated south with young.
Semi cloudy day- temp is 60 degrees- winds are west and mild.  Two fishing boats on lake.  Weeds along shoreline increasing along with muck bottom- two sea gulls spotted on the lake.
Foggy morning- 70 F- algal bloom appears minimal- lake level receding- more weeds and vegetation growth increasing along shoreline.
Cloudy  rain day .575"- air temp 52- SE winds- minimal algal bloom- 6 mallards- 3 sea gulls
Temp is 39 degrees- wind is southwest- algal bloom at medium level- sunny day.  Lake level still reading.
Air temp 38- NW winds mild- colorama in full view- Canadian geese moving south with ducks- hummingbirds

Semi-cloudy day temp is 76 degrees- winds are mild- south.  Algal bloom seems minimal- lake is calm - no white caps.  Blue heron spotted near the shore- 5 mallard ducks- 1 loon- 8 purple martins at the bird house.
Algal bloom minimal.  Temp. 64 degrees-winds mild westerly.  Today I spotted 1 bald eagle- 6 mergansers and a pair of mallard ducks.
Winds south- temp. 68 degrees.  Spotted blue heron- 6 mallard ducks.  Lake calm- sunny day- algal bloom minimal.
Sunny day- temp. 84 degrees- winds se- white caps on lake.  Lake water clear.  Spotted bald eagle over lake.  Swimming + boating excellent.
Algal bloom is minimal.  Sunny day temp is 74 degrees- winds are south and mild- spotted bald eagle over the lake- one loon- blue heron and several mallard ducks.
Sunny day- temp. 73 degrees- winds northwest.  Algal bloom minimal.  Many boats on lake.  Heavy rains earlier today.
Temp. 65 degrees.  Winds southwest.  Rain today.  Algal bloom slightly increasing.  Spotted blue heron and bald eagle over lake.

Temperature is 66 degrees- winds are NW and mild.  Algae bloom minimal- spotted mallard duck and family of 8 chicks- 1 blue heron- 1 bald eagle- purple martens left the area with their young on 7/25/94
Temp. 54 degrees.  Winds southwest.  Lake rough white caps.  Semi cloudy day.  Algal bloom minimal.  Few boats + fishermen on lake.  Rain today .510".
Temp. 66 degrees.  Winds southwest.  Semi cloudy day.  Lake calm + slight algal bloom present.  Three sea gulls and bald eagle sighted.
Sunny day.  Temp. 66 degrees.  Winds NE + rough white caps on lake.  Algal level increased.  Spotted 2 seagulls + blue heron today.
Sunny day- temp. 66 degrees- winds northeast.  Lake conditions on algal bloom increased.  White caps on lake.
Sunny day - temperature is 62 degrees- wind NE and mild.  Algal bloom increased- family of mallard ducks on the lake- 2 sea gulls and a bald eagle spotted on the lake.
Sunny day- temp. 73 degrees- winds SW and mild.  Algal bloom decreasing.  Spotted bald eagle + some seagulls over lake.

Cloudy day- rain in the forecast.  Temp is 49 degrees- winds are northwest- algal bloom minimal.  Several boats and fishermen on the lake- spotted several families of mallard ducks.  Also spotted a bald eagle.
Sunny day- temp is 52 degrees- winds are SW and mild- several sea gulls spotted on the lake and several bufferhead ducks- one bald eagle sighted over the lake.  Algal level is minimal.
Sunny day- temp. 72 degrees- winds mild southwest- lake calm.  Bald eagle sighted and one pair of mallard ducks.
Temp. 72 degrees- winds mild northeast.  Sunny day.  Algal bloom minimal.  Spotted four sea gulls and one blue heron on lake.  Martins nesting with young at bird house.
Temp 72 degrees- sunny day- winds mild se.  Sighted blue heron- one pair mallard ducks on lake.  White tail deer sighted on lake shore.  Some algal bloom.

Temp is 79 degrees- semi cloudy day- (rain in forecast) .  Winds are mild southwest- algal bloom is minimal- sighted several sea gulls- blue herons- several mallard ducks on the lake- one white tail deer on the shore.
Sunny day- temp. 69 degrees- winds mild N.  Algal bloom minimal.  Sighted bald eagle- two merganser ducks and two deer fawns on lake shores.

Semi-cloudy day- temp is 71 degrees- winds are mild and from the southeast.  Algal bloom minimal- plant life is good and adequate.  Spotted one white tail deer- two sea gulls and a bald eagle on the lake.
Overcast day- temp. 75 degrees- winds mild S.  Algal bloom very pronounced along shore.  Spotted family of five mallard ducks today.
Semi-cloudy day- temp is 72 degrees- winds are mild southeast.- algae bloom is minimal near the shoreline.  Spotted 3 bald eagles on the shoreline of marsh area.  Spotted 5 sea gulls on the lake.
Temp. 49 degrees- cloudy day + rain.  Winds southwest- several bald eagles spotted over lake- geese flying south.
Bright clear- sunny some algal bloom.
Water had turned- lots of algal blooms in water.
Very clear- no wind and the lake smooth.
Three days before it had been very windy. The three days before it had been very windy.
windy - lots of pollen a few days ago
5 MPH wind- bright. 5 MPH wind- bright.
partly cloudy and breezy. 2 inches of rain previous evening
60% cloud cover. 68 degrees. surface water temp 76 degrees F.
partly cloudy/hazy. 70 degrees air temperature. 73.3 degrees surface water temperature.
Clear and sunny. About 70 degrees F.
Considerable algae present considerable algae present   Algae present
Was put under Clark Lake station 153112 even though the Field ID and description said Anvil. Sample coincides with an Anvil field sample. Changed to Anvil Deep site (1/23/2015- AEB).
Donna DePape was additional helper.  Wavy- clouds in blue sky- NW winds approx. 12 mph.  Some but not alot of boating.
Donna DePape was additional helper.  W. winds ~ 15 mph.  Partly cloudy.  Very wavy.  Recent rains.
Wavy.  Boat activity high.  Mats of filamentous algae throughout lake...affects swimming.
winds from west around 15 mph.  wavy.
Sunny day and soft wind from NW.
partly cloudy-  some wind- not rained in a few days- few boat waves.  Floating milfoil abundant  especially from the north bay.
gusty windy approx. 15 mph-  many waves from boats and wind- mostly cloudy.  Lake loaded with floating milfoil. D.O. meter not working properly for D.0. but okay for temperature.
6 to 10 mph winds WNW- partly cloudy but threatening rain- not many boat waves.

column1: D.O. meter still not working correctly for D.O. but okay for temp. (borrowed from Vilas Co. Ext. again.)

column2: Slight wind ENE- few boat waves- sunny.  Borrowed working D.O. meter from Kay Scharpf - Franklin Lake.  Donna DePape helped monitor.
D.O. meter that we borrow from Vilas Cnty extension now working adequately.

column1: Donna DePape assist as she has all summer.
Eagles- merganzers- mallards- muskrats and 1 otter.

column2: Wind light and variable. Sunny. Both loon pairs on nest. Donna DePape helped.
